RADIUS機能、LDAP機能、CA（証明書）機能を１台に搭載した専用アプライアンス

・Web／MAC／IEEE802.1X認証に対応し、外部LDAP／Active Directory連携やRADIUSプロキシ連携に対応

・証明書発行機能(CA機能)をサポートし、スマートデバイスの証明書も発行可能

・ユーザー自身による利用ID・端末・証明書申請、管理者による審査（許可／却下）、MACアドレス自動登録、ユーザーへのパスワード有効期限通知、未使用アカウントの自動削除、一括アカウント申請＆発行など、アカウント運用管理負荷を軽減し、認証システム全体の運用コストを削減

・1対N構成による冗長構成に対応

・syslog管理サーバー（LOG＠Adapter+）と連携し、不正な通信をしたアカウントをブラックリスト登録し接続拒否

・Shibboleth SPオプションにより、ネットワーク認証とクラウド認証のシングルサインオンに対応

Simple Management Leads to Faster Recoveries and Faster DevOps

Actifio Global Manager in Azure helps you manage copies of production data to speed up data protection and disaster recovery, as well as test data provisioning for DevOps.

How it works

Actifio Global Manager (AGM) is a powerful management platform for the Actifio’s Sky appliance. AGM provides a single pane of glass view of all Actifio Sky Appliances existing in Azure, on-premises or any other public cloud, and it offers a Google-like search capability to find and recovery protected files.

AGM incorporates advanced management functionality including:
  • Global Search - AGM provides a simple Google-like search interface to enable users to easily find and restore files and folders
  • Robust API - Easily extend upon AGM with Actifio’s powerful API
  • Global View - Gain a single view into all Actifio systems operating in your environment.
  • Easy to use - Leveraging advanced HTML5 technologies, AGM provides a simplified user experience while delivering enterprise class protection
  • Scale Out - Manage tens or hundreds of Actifio Sky appliances through a single interface including advanced filtering
  • Advanced alerting - Get automated alerting for protection jobs that are not meeting SLA requirements
  • Powerful SLA Management - Implement and enforce SLAs across the environment
  • Role-based Access Controls - AGM integrates with existing directories to ensure that access controls are consistently enforced and to prevent unauthorized data access

Requirements, Contact & Trial

AGM requires one or more Actifio Sky appliances to operate. Actifio offers a complimentary 30-day Sky trial license for up to 5TB of data in Azure which is supported by AGM.

The minimum Azure resources required for AGM are:
  • Without Catalog: D4s_v3 and 50GB disk
  • With Catalog: D8s_v3 and 700GB disk

Faster to Azure, Faster Recoveries, Faster DevOps

Actifio helps you use Azure to manage copies of production data to speed up data protection and disaster recovery, as well as test data provisioning for DevOps.

How it works

The Actifio Sky appliance captures application data in its native application format, at the block level using APIs, creates a gold master copy of the data (the full backup). Actifio then incrementally updates that master copy with changed blocks, and virtualizes the data so virtual copies can be mounted or provisioned for recoveries, dev/test, analytics or any other use case.

To manage and move that data, administrators set up and apply SLA templates for the application to dictate how often it is updated from production (incremental snapshots), how long the data is retained for instant mounting, how long it is kept locally in a deduped and compressed state, and how often it is replicated to another Actifio appliance (in Azure or another site), or an object storage bucket. The SLA also dictates how long application data is retained at the target site, and how (in a ready-to-use format, or in a deduped state).

For more information on Actifio Sky, please refer to the materials linked at the bottom of this page.

Sizing, Contact & Trial

An Actifio rep. or partner can help size the appropriate Actifio solution for your needs, and help you with a trial and purchase. For assistance, please email Azure@actifio.com, or call 855-886-8997. You can also begin your trial of Actifio Sky on Azure with a complimentary 30-day license for up to 5 TB of data right now.

Best Practice

Deploy only the specified compute instance(s) to have the proper memory and disk resources. Depending on the managed data set size and performance requirements, use D3_v2, D4_v2 and/or D5_v2; or for SSDs: DS3_v2, DS4_v2, or DS5_v2.

Enterprise 5.0 SP2 Linux","description":"

100% .NET / .NET Core

Bring Your Own License (BYOL)

NCache is an In-Memory Distributed Cache for .NET / .NET Core. NCache is a high-performance object caching solution for mission critical .NET / .NET Core applications with real time data access needs. Whether you need to cache once and read multiple times reference data or frequently updated transactional data, NCache is your applications in memory data store of choice.

Key Features:

  • ASP.NET / ASP.NET Core Sessions
  • Distributed Caching. Cache app data to reduce expensive database trips
  • Pub/Sub Messaging & Continuous Queries
  • Sync Cache with SQL Server & Oracle Databases
  • Search Cache with SQL/LINQ Queries
  • EF Core Cache thru Extension Methods for NCache
  • Dynamic Self-Healing Peer to Peer Clustering (not a Master/Slave)
  • WAN Replication across multiple datacenters (Azure Regions)
  • Client Cache (InProc Speed) on top of a cache cluster

Arista vEOS Router fully integrates with Arista CloudVision centralized provisioning and visibility to simplify the experience of deploying and managing cloud services with a network-wide approach to workload orchestration and workflow automation.

Whether on premises or in the cloud, the Arista vEOS Router helps enterprises and service providers build the best possible hybrid cloud networks without compromising security, reliability, and performance.

For a free 60-day trial license, to purchase a BYOL licenses, and for general inquiries please visit our website or contact Arista Networks at sales@arista.com.

The Node:

Running the IRI software enables your device to communicate with neighbors in the peer-to-peer network that the Tangle operates on. Any device connected to the network.


What is IRI?

The IOTA Reference implementation, commonly known as IRI, is the reference implementation of the IOTA 'node' software in Java. The IRI software enables the Tangle to operate by enabling individuals to run the software and operate a Node.

https://docs.iota.org/iri

Why run a Node?

It encourages decentralization of the network, and removes the need to trust a third party node to access the Tangle.

The purpose of this project is to provide an easy-to-deploy Flamenco manager/worker environment that can be plugged into Blender Cloud. Referencing the architecture diagram here ( https://www.flamenco.io/docs/developer_docs/architecture/ ) , this project covers the "remote farm" component.

This marketplace image serves the "render vm" role in the worker pool. Other components of this project are the Flamenco Manager VM image, a deployment template that creates the complete "remote farm" with vnet, manager, and worker, and an evaluation deployment template that can fit all the components within an Azure free trial subscription.

Just releasing for Windows at the moment.
  • Flamenco Worker 2.3
  • Blender 2.79

See the project page for more information and updates.

https://www.atlgaming.net/blender-flamenco-azure.html

----

Original install bits available in c:\atlg\installs
Flamenco worker config backup c:\atlg\flamenco-worker.cfg
Worker is expecting a manager at http://10.0.0.4:8083
Shortcut to worker is on desktop and runs
C:\flamenco-worker\flamenco-worker.exe

Getting started

As a Linux-based security appliance, there are a few differences between it and a typical server running on Azure:

  • Appliance administration is typically done via a web user interface pointed at http://[DNS]:8000 or http://[PublicIP]:8000
  • The username to login to the appliance web user interface is admin and the password is the one you have configured on Azure portal while deploying the VM.
  • This Barracuda WAF Control Center is licensed using the Bring-Your-Own-License (BYOL) model. Fill out the evaluation form here or at web user interface of appliance to receive a 30-day evaluation license or purchase one of the licenses depending on your requirement.

Click here for more details on deployment instructions. For any issues related to Barracuda Product(s) contact Barracuda Support.

As part of Cisco's Cloud connect portfolio, the Bring Your Own License (BYOL) version of Cisco® Catalyst® 8000V Edge Software (Catalyst 8000V) delivers the maximum performance for virtual enterprise-class networking services in Azure cloud. This image supports all the Catalyst 8000V (C8000V) DNA packages and uses the high-performance versions of Azure instances with direct I/O path for higher & more consistent SDWAN performance. The C8000V is a full feature Cisco IOS XE router and enables enterprise IT to deploy the same enterprise-class networking services in Azure similar to features used to on-prem networks. It enables enterprise-class Routing, VPN, Firewall, High-Availability, IP SLA, AVC, WAN Opt, and more. The familiar IOS XE CLI and RESTful API ensure easy deployment, monitoring, troubleshooting, and service orchestration. To activate, please obtain a DNA license from Cisco. Learn more about Cisco's cloud portfolio: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/cloud/overview.html.

You have selected the Bring Your Own License (BYOL) version of the Cisco Cloud Services Router (CSR) 1000V. The BYOL version supports all four CSR Technology Packages (IP Base, SEC, AppX, and AX), depending on the installed license. A valid license must be purchased from Cisco, or a Cisco partner.

Without a license installed, the BYOL version of the CSR 1000V will be completely functional and will have all features enabled. It will however be limited to a total throughput of 100 Kbps until an evaluation license or purchased license is installed. If you would like to request a 60-day evaluation license please visit the self-service license tool listed in the links section of this page, and perform the following steps:

  1. Using the pull-down menu on the right-hand side of the evaluation licensing page, select “Demo and Evaluation”.
  2. Enter “Cloud Services Router” into the search box.
  3. The tool will ask for a UDI Serial Number, which is a unique identifier generated by each CSR. Entering “show license udi” on any CSR will provide you with this string.

The Cisco Technical Assistance Center (TAC) provides 24x7 phone and email support to users of the CSR 1000V BYOL version. This level of support is only available after a license is purchased from Cisco or a reseller.

Community support is available during the 60-day evaluation period at the URL listed in the links section of this page.

Have questions? We’d love to chat! Contact the CSR 1000V product team by emailing ask-csr-azure-pm@cisco.com.

You have selected the Bring Your Own License (BYOL) version of the Cisco Cloud Services Router (CSR) 1000V. The BYOL version supports all four CSR Technology Packages (IP Base, SEC, AppX, and AX), depending on the installed license. A valid license must be purchased from Cisco, or a Cisco partner.

Without a license installed, the BYOL version of the CSR 1000V will be completely functional and will have all features enabled. It will however be limited to a total throughput of 100 Kbps until an evaluation license or purchased license is installed. If you would like to request a 60-day evaluation license please visit the self-service license tool listed in the links section of this page, and perform the following steps:

  1. Using the pull-down menu on the right-hand side of the evaluation licensing page, select “Demo and Evaluation”.
  2. Enter “Cloud Services Router” into the search box.
  3. The tool will ask for a UDI Serial Number, which is a unique identifier generated by each CSR. Entering “show license udi” on any CSR will provide you with this string.

The Cisco Technical Assistance Center (TAC) provides 24x7 phone and email support to users of the CSR 1000V BYOL version. This level of support is only available after a license is purchased from Cisco or a reseller.

Community support is available during the 60-day evaluation period at the URL listed in the links section of this page.

Have questions? We’d love to chat! Contact the CSR 1000V product team by emailing ask-csr-azure-pm@cisco.com.

    Within the Airlock Secure Access Hub, Airlock Gateway provides the platform for the central security entry point for protected applications.

    Depending on the license, it provides the following functionality:

    • Airlock WAF - Web Application Firewall
      • Analysing traffic moving between users and services
      • Blocking attempted attacks on applications before they can reach the protected systems
      • Comprehensive protection against the OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities
      • Fraud detection
      • Threat intelligence
      • BOT detection
      • Virtual patching
      • Load balancing and fail-over
      • Enforce role-based access control (RBAC) on all application access
      • Enable centralised management of security policies
    • Airlock API - API Security Gateway
      • Protects the endpoints of your modern web applications
      • Enforces API Specification
      • Prevents invalid & unauthorized requests
      • Blocks API attacks
      • DevSecOps: guaranteed safe DevOps

F5 BIG-IP Virtual Edition - GOOD - includes F5's BIG-IP Local Traffic Manager (LTM).

BIG-IP LTM provides advanced L4–L7 traffic management services including local server load balancing with support for a broad range of persistence methods, algorithms, and protocols beyond HTTP/TCP (e.g., HTTP/2, UDP, etc.). It also provides SSL/TLS termination and offloading, deep health monitoring, and connection state management. As a full application proxy with granular programmability, BIG-IP enables customized L7 inspection, traffic steering, and content switching for greater agility and flexibility. Automated deployments are enabled via REST APIs and Azure Application Resource Manager (ARM) templates.

Watch our BIG-IP VE Deployment Demo in Azure, or for more information, go to Modules.

To deploy alternate BIG-IP versions use our ARM templates on F5's GitHub site

Hyper Scale Security for Hyper Scalable Cloud Environments

Whether your data and applications are stored on-site, in a data center, or in the public cloud (or a combination of all three), organizations still need to meet their requirements of security, control, compliance, and governance. The on-demand nature of public cloud such as Azure where workloads move and regroup, means that maintaining continuous visibility and control over the rapid changes calls for expert intervention.

Common security challenges include:

  • Centralized visibility and threat management for your hybrid environment
  • Deploy applications and workloads securely
  • Manage access and control privileges to cloud and on-premises workloads
  • Secure data transfer, data migrations
  • Accomplish all security deployments at the pace and scale demanded by cloud architectures.

Connectivity of sensors, edge devices, gateways, their buffering capacity, energy harvesting, battery and the build compatibility with each other, can all be sources of large numbers of menaces in supporting the IoT system. Let’s just see a list of how many ways things can go wrong in a practical IoT system: 1) Wireless connectivity can go down 2) Sensor/Edge device may need power rebooting 3) Sensor and Edge may have incompatible build 4) Edge analytics need a special update for a couple of devices 5) You sold a sensor two years ago and now the customer is bringing it online (can happen in Industrial IoT) 6) JSON (or any other format) is not reaching the cloud (can be a connection or edge build issue) 7) Edge build is crashing 8) API is failing after a minor update in an edge All the above issues are not a stretch of the imagination. Any practical edge-driven IoT system faces these issues day in and out. If, A-H has to be managed manually, there is absolutely no way one can build any IoT system in scale. Just assume 100 sensors and 100 edges in a system in a factory. A very modest scale IoT system. A simple combinatorial analysis will show that the factory can experience 3200 IoT failures! That’s in a single factory. As the number of sensors will grow in a system, say to 10,000, the total number of failures will exceed 320,000. It is impossible to manually manage such a complex system without automation of the IoT support system. SignaGuard (MachineSense®) has built and implemented a scalable IoT system for Novatec for the last 4 years and has learned how to manage A-H in the field via various levels of automation tools. SignaDiag is a set of automation tools to manage your IoT system in scale. Enterprise & Free Edition BYOL for CPU","description":"Whether you're a freelancer writing code, a data science professional who wants to try before you buy, or an enterprise CIO, OmniSci makes it easy for you and your team to get started with Big Data analytics!

OmniSci (formerly MapD) is the pioneer in accelerated analytics. The OmniSci platform is used in business and government to find insights in data beyond the limits of mainstream analytics tools. Harnessing the massive parallelism of modern CPU and GPU hardware, the platform is available in the cloud and on-premise.

Key Benefits:

  • Real-Time Interaction - OmniSci wants everyone to be curious about data and easily explore hypotheses – to ask question upon question, without curiosity-defeating latency.
  • Conventional and Geo Data - OmniSci bridges the divide between traditional business intelligence tools (BI) and geographic information systems (GIS), making location intelligence a first-class citizen of big data analytics.
  • Data Science workflows - Leverage native SQL, interactive visual analytics, extensive PyData stack integrations, and a powerful machine learning framework.

Who uses OmniSci?
OmniSci is being used to dramatically accelerate big data analytics in telecom, financial services, defense and intelligence, automotive, retail, pharmaceutical, advertising, academia, and other fields that demand rapid insights. It is the favorite solution of Big Data Analysts, Geospatial Analysts and Data Scientists. OmniSci originated from research at the MIT Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory (CSAIL)

Science Virtual Machine - Windows Server 2019","description":"

The 'Data Science Virtual Machine (DSVM)' is a 'Windows Server 2019 with Containers' VM that has several popular tools for data exploration, analysis, modeling & development pre installed.

Highlights:

Operating System, Drivers and other base components

  • "Windows Server 2019 with Containers" image from Azure Marketplace
  • Nvidia drivers, CUDA Toolkit, cuDNN (when GPU machines are used)
  • Windows Subsystem for Linux (version 1)
  • Docker (Windows docker images only)
  • Anaconda ("conda")
  • Git

Authoring Tools

  • Visual Studio Code
  • Visual Studio 2019 Community Edition
  • PyCharm Community Edition
  • Jupyter, Jupyter Lab
  • RStudio
  • Power BI Desktop
  • Weka

ML Framework

  • PyTorch, TensorFlow, scikit-learn
  • pyspark
  • Vowpal Wabbit

Other Notable Components

  • Azure CLI
  • Azure ML SDK for Python
  • Azure Storage Explorer
  • SQL Server 2019 Developer Edition
  • Microsoft 365 BYOL (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Teams)

Users can access the DSVM via Remote Desktop or SSH. Optionally, the VM can be placed in a corporate network.

Users have full access to the DSVM. If needed, configurations can be adjusted, and additional frameworks can be installed like with any other virtual machine. The image provided here is a static VM image. Maintenance and protection against vulnerabilities of provisioned DSVMs is in the customer's responsibility.

There is also a DSVM on Ubuntu.

For more details, see the Data Science Virtual Machine documentation.

Highlights:

Operating System, Drivers and other base components

Authoring Tools

  • dask

  • Azure CLI
  • Azure ML SDK for Python
  • Azure Storage Explorer

Windows 10 Enterprise for Virtual Desktop + Microsoft 365 Apps is a multi-session Windows 10 capability enabled only by the Windows Virtual Desktop service. Both the service and the multi-session capability are available. Windows 10 multi-session capability is only available on Azure and, even then, only when used with the Windows Virtual Desktop service.

Windows Virtual Desktop is a managed desktop and application virtualization service hosted on Azure. Windows 10 Enterprise for Virtual Desktop is a multi-session Windows 10 capability enabled only by the Windows Virtual Desktop service. Both the service and the multi-session capability are available. Windows 10 multi-session capability is only available on Azure and, even then, only when used with the Windows Virtual Desktop service.

Windows Virtual Desktop is a managed desktop and application virtualization service hosted on Azure. Windows Virtual Desktop delivers the best virtual desktop experience by providing remote access to modern desktop and applications from any device. Combined with Microsoft 365 and Azure, it provides users with multi-session Windows 10 and Office 365 ProPlus, a secure computing experience with unmatched scale and reduced IT costs.

Access to Windows Virtual Desktop comes at no additional charge for Microsoft 365 E3 and E5, and Windows E3 and E5 customers. Once you have the appropriate licenses, set up an Azure subscription (or use an existing one), and you are ready to quickly deploy and manage your modern desktops and apps.

Windows Server 2022 Datacenter brings innovation to Windows Server that enables customers to run their existing and new business critical applications with confidence on Azure, on-premises and at the edge. Windows Server 2022 Datacenter brings the latest in security innovation, unique hybrid capabilities, and enhancements for modern applications. As a part of the release, we are bringing Secured-core to Windows Server to secure systems running applications and services on Windows Server 2022. Secured-core builds on technologies such as System Guard and Windows Server Virtualization-based Security to minimize risk from firmware vulnerabilities and advanced malware. Windows Server 2022 includes updates to Storage Migration Service that allow customers to seamlessly migrate file servers from NetApp FAS to Windows Server. The new release also provides increased file server security and performance with SMB AES-256 encryption and SMB on-the-fly compression. Furthermore, this release packs in significant improvements to Windows container runtime such as cross-version compatibility and containerization tools for .NET, ASP.NET and IIS applications.

Windows Server 2022 Datacenter brings innovation to Windows Server that enables customers to run their existing and new business critical applications with confidence on Azure, on-premises and at the edge. Windows Server 2022 Datacenter brings the latest in security innovation, unique hybrid capabilities, and enhancements for modern applications. As a part of the release, we are bringing Secured-core to Windows Server to secure systems running applications and services on Windows Server 2022. Secured-core builds on technologies such as System Guard and Windows Server Virtualization-based Security to minimize risk from firmware vulnerabilities and advanced malware. Windows Server 2022 includes updates to Storage Migration Service that allow customers to seamlessly migrate file servers from NetApp FAS to Windows Server. The new release also provides increased file server security and performance with SMB AES-256 encryption and SMB on-the-fly compression. Furthermore, this release packs in significant improvements to Windows container runtime such as cross-version compatibility and containerization tools for .NET, ASP.NET and IIS applications.

This awi MX Azure Virtual Machine allows you to quickly and easily deploy an awi MX Enterprise Edition Server. The Virtual Machine image comes complete with awi MX server components pre-installed. All you have to do is enter your awi MX Enterprise Edition licence to complete the installation and the server is then ready to be configured and used. Please note that SQL Server and the MX Configuration Database is not included so you will need to install the configuration database on a separate instance of SQL and attach the server to the database. Please see the Azure Deployment Guide in the NDL User Area for more information.

\n\n

This MX Server can be used in a live, test or development environment, as part of a new MX installation or expanding an existing MX installation, in accordance with your Enterprise Edition licensing agreement with NDL.

\n\n

This Azure Virtual Machine image comes with the following pre-installed components:

\n
  • Microsoft Windows Server 2016
    • \n
  • MX App Server
    • \n
  • MX App Manager
    • \n
  • NDL awi Licence Editor
\n\n

Please note that once you have created a VM from the supplied image you are responsible for the configuration, security and maintenance of the VM, including installing any updates.

Please note that SQL Server and the MX Configuration Database is not included so you will need to install the configuration database on a separate instance of SQL and attach the server to the database. Please see the Azure Deployment Guide in the NDL User Area for more information.

\n\n

This MX Server can be used in a live, test or development environment, as part of a new MX installation or expanding an existing MX installation, in accordance with your Public Store Edition licensing agreement with NDL.

\n\n

This Azure Virtual Machine image comes with the following pre-installed components:

\n
  • Microsoft Windows Server 2016
    • \n
  • MX App Server
    • \n
  • MX App Manager
    • \n
  • NDL awi Licence Editor
\n\n

2.2.0-00 Release Software","description":"A brief listing of new features and functionalities are available in its Release-notes posted in below URL:
https://docs.nebbiolo.io/fogOS2.2.0/release-notes/release-notes/
 
General features and functions introduced
Upgrade of fogNodes with Virtual Assets using fogSM UI
OT VM Backup and Recovery using fogSM UI
UI based fogSM Metrics monitoring
Support for NFN-50 x86 based Hardware Platform
Security Enhancement for fogNode Registration
 
New Software Support
 
Upgrade of fogNodes with Virtual Assets using fogSM UI: 
The new and improved fogSM UI offers an easy-to-use interface for upgrading the fogNodes to a newer version with zero-touch on fogNodes. As a part of upgrade preparation, a fogSM with newer version is launched with a cloned snapshot of the current fogSM, so that all required data can be carried forward. Once the new fogSM is available, an entry pointing to the new fogSM is configured on the original fogSM and system will be ready for upgrade. Now the appropriate fogNode can be selected and with a click of Upgrade button, the fogNode gets upgraded to the newer version and registers with the newer fogSM. Once all the fogNodes are upgraded, the older fogSM can be unprovisioned.
 
OT VM Backup and Recovery using fogSM UI: 
The feature allows the user to back-up the OT-VMs that are hosted on fogNodes. The operation is triggered from the AppStore of fogSM where specific VM (that is provisioned on the fogSM) offers a Snapshot button that triggers a backup to be taken on the selected fogNode on which the OT-VM is deployed. The functionality details are documented in the chapter along with the Videos.
 
UI based fogSM Metrics monitoring: 
fogSM metrics page allows administrator to monitor the resource (CPU, memory, disk, network) usage of the fogSM and offers visibility into functioning of various processes, docker containers, databus usage, database utilization and http request / responses with turnaround times. <h2>Usage Instructions</h2>Important: You must use OnCommand Cloud Manager to launch Cloud Volumes ONTAP environments. You cannot launch Cloud Volumes ONTAP directly from the Azure portal, as the Cloud Volumes ONTAP system will not be deployed correctly. <ol>
  <li>
	  Create an account on the <a href="https://portal.nice.de">NiCE Portal</a>.<br>
	  If you are already registered, proceed with the next step.
  </li>
  <li>
	  In your account, request access to the <b>NiCE Active 365 Monitor for Azure</b>.
  </li>
  <li>
	  Upon approval of your registration by the <i>NiCE Solutions Team</i>, you will receive an e-mail notification.<br>

  </li>
  <li>
	  In the meantime, you may deploy the VM associated with this plan.
  </li>
  <li>

  <li>

  </i>
  <li>
	  Execute the command <b>nice-bootloader Active365MonAz</b>.<br>
      The tool asks for your credentials in the <i>NiCE Portal</i>, then connects to the portal, downloads, and installs<br>
      the packages for the <b>NiCE Active 365 Monitor for Azure</b>.
  </li>
  <li>
	  The remaining configuration is described in the <b>NiCE Active 365 Monitor for Azure - Quick Start Guide</b>,<br>
	  which may be found in your download area in the <i>NiCE Portal</i>.
  </li>
</ol>

Memcached is an in-memory key-value store for small chunks of arbitrary data (strings, objects) from results of database calls, API calls, or page rendering. The simplicity of its design promotes quick deployment, ease of development, and solves many problems facing large data caches. Its API is available for most popular languages.

    Niles Partners is launching a product which will configure and publish Memcache, to produce free implementations of distributed or otherwise scalable and high availability which is embedded pre-configured tool and ready-to-launch Machine image on Azure that contains MariaDB.

Memcached basically runs on Unix-like operating systems and on Microsoft Windows. It depends on the libevent library.
 

A large hash table is provided by its APIs. Applications using Memcached typically layer requests and additions into RAM before falling back on a slower backing store, such as a database.

This is the general knowledge that one must have before started working on Memcache.

Let us now know what exactly its software architecture is and what its functionalities are.

Software architecture

The system uses a client-server architecture. The servers maintain a key–value associative-array; the clients populate this array and query it by key. The length of the Keys are up to 250 bytes and values can be at most 1 megabyte in size.

If we talk about the typical deployment of this architecture then it can have several servers and many clients. However, it is possible to use Memcached on a single computer, acting simultaneously as client and server. The size of its hash table is often very large. It is limited to available memory across all the servers in the cluster of servers in a data center. We are launching a product which will configure and publish Spark MLlib, an open source software solution which is embedded pre-configured tool with Ubuntu OS and ready-to-launch VM on Azure that contains Spark MBlib, Hadoop 2.7, Scala, Linux, PHP (LAMP).
MLlib fits into Spark's APIs and interoperates with Scala. You can use any Hadoop data source (e.g. HDFS, HBase, or local files), making it easy to plug into Hadoop workflows.

Why MLlib? It is built on Apache Spark, which is a fast and general engine for large scale processing. Supposedly, running times or up to 100x faster than Hadoop MapReduce, or 10x faster on disk. Supports writing applications in Java, Scala, or Python.

MLlib contains many algorithms and utilities
Classification: logistic regression, naive Bayes
Regression: generalized linear regression, survival regression
Decision trees, random forests, and gradient-boosted trees
Recommendation: alternating least squares (ALS)
Clustering: K-means, Gaussian mixtures (GMMs)
Topic modeling: latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA)
Frequent itemsets, association rules, and sequential pattern mining
MLlib will still support the RDD-based API in spark.mllib with bug fixes.
MLlib will not add new features to the RDD-based API.
In the Spark 2.x releases, MLlib will add features to the DataFrames-based API to reach feature parity with the RDD-based API.
After reaching feature parity (roughly estimated for Spark 2.2), the RDD-based API will be deprecated.
The RDD-based API is expected to be removed in Spark 3.0.
DataFrames provide a more user-friendly API than RDDs.     RemoteScan Enterprise makes it easy to connect your scanners to an Azure Cloud environment.  It allows you to scan documents directly from within applications that are hosted in Azure, significantly reducing the number of steps required to get the scanned image to the virtual machine or server. With RemoteScan, scanned images are never stored on the physical endpoint– they are immediately transmitted to the Azure server, supporting a secure, compliant document scanning workflow.

    Features

    • Works with all TWAIN- and WIA-compliant scanners, Fujitsu ScanSnaps, cameras, and image capture devices
    • Enables fast scan speeds while maintaining image quality
    • Uses the secure virtual channels to transmit images
    • Allows you to lock down scanner settings to limit impact on network
    • Works with all TWAIN-compliant scanning applications
    • Allows scanners to be shared – any scanner can become a network scanner with RemoteScan

    RemoteScan will provide 30 days free licensing before new licensing must be purchased and applied.

    RocketML ParallelCluster uses a simple text file to model and provision all the resources needed for your HPC applications in an automated and secure manner. It supports the Slurm job scheduler for easy job submissions.

    ####Benefits: #####Easy Resource Scaling You can use a simple text file to model, provision, scale, start, and stop the resources needed for your applications in an automated and secure manner. #####Easy Cluster Management With Azure ParallelCluster you can provision resources in a safe, repeatable manner, allowing you to build and rebuild your infrastructure without the need for manual actions or custom scripts. #####Seamless Migration to the Cloud Azure Parallel Cluster supports Ubuntu18.04 LTS and Slurm job schedulers so you can migrate your on-prem HPC workloads to Azure. ####Audience: Researchers and Engineers who use HPC on-prem or on AWS can use Azure ParallelCluster for fast and seamless migration.","iconUrl":"https://store-images.s-microsoft.com/image/apps.40492.a3a6cd15-3f8c-4415-8058-b6f38fb3565c.e4faf64d-473f-42bf-acbf-a3224a139cb1.f6b56eed-b987-4327-bb6c-ed0970cc68d0","author":"RocketML Inc","osType":"Linux","plan":"hpcvm002","offer":"rocketml_azure_parallel_cluster_hpc_vm","publisher":"rocketml","sku":"hpcvm002","version":"latest","osState":"Generalized"},"id":"/subscriptions/63d7e191-c910-43ba-908f-252519936998/resourceGroups/powershell-sdk-testing/providers/Microsoft.LabServices/labPlans/labplan-unit-powershell/images/rocketml.rocketml_azure_parallel_cluster_hpc_vm.hpcvm002","name":"rocketml.rocketml_azure_parallel_cluster_hpc_vm.hpcvm002","type":"Microsoft.LabServices/labPlans/images"},{"properties":{"provisioningState":"Succeeded","displayName":"Rocket Discover","description":"Rocket Discover provides business users with an intuitive, end-to-end data discovery and exploration experience: from data preparation to data discovery and simple reporting. Users can easily transform disparate data sources such as IBM Cognos TM1, IBM Cognos BI, Mainframe data and local flat files into a single result set for visualization, by leveraging simple data transformations. An intuitive dashboarding interface that includes drag-and-drop features, allows users to create, modify, and drill down on data visualizations that are displayed on a dashboard. When deploying this plan, we will spin up an Azure VM with a SEPPmail Appliance.

Configuration:

Disks

The VM will be deployed with one initial disk for OS and the appliance. If you plan to use Large File Transfer (LFT), add another disk with size and performance as needed later. We recommend a disk size of 30GB and up for LFT.

Networking

We deploy the VM in an existing virtual network of your choice, or a new one you may create at deployment. A more advanced network configuration can be done after the initial deployment.

The following ports will be opened to the public internet:

  • Port 25 - SMTP

    • We need this port so that your E-mail system is able to send E-mails to the appliance and SEPPmail can send them for delivery.

  • Port 8443 - Admin GUI

    • Access to the Administration portal of the Appliance

  • Port 443 - GINA Portal

    • Our award-winning GINA encryption portal for spontaenous, low frequency encryption.

Depending on your infrastructure and additional features you want to use, there may be other ports you need to open later on. Refer to the manual for further information.

High Availability

SEPPmail allows clustering on application level. If you want high availability, deploy a second SEPPmail appliance and refer to the manual on docs.seppmail.com how to configure clusters.

Identity Maestro - Identity Management from a Single Web Portal

Light-weight Identity Maestro server that provides a web management portal, to allow tier-one service desk staff to manage users and groups with requiring elevated administrator privileges. Designed for SMB customers, K-12 schools & districts, private schools, colleges and universities who need to run small service desk teams to assist large user pools.

Just imagine:

  • collapsing multiple management portals for the many online services and on-premise applications into a single management interface in a browser,
  • delegating user management tasks to non-IT staff without granting those people with privileged administrator access to anything,
  • freeing up time for your IT staff so that they can focus on the bigger picture of IT infrastructure management and security, and
  • providing a user self-service web portal where they can reset their own passwords. Supports automatically unlocking locked users accounts and allowing users with expired passwords to reset their password.

Add this Windows server 2012 R2 VM to your Azure subscription and refer to our setup and configurtion guide for instructions to get started.

The installer file and documentation is also available in a Identity Maestro Get Started folder on the rroot of the C drive.

This VM supports RDP access.

Feel free to contact our team for assistance to get you started setting up your Identity Maestro Management Portal.

Silver Peak VX software use the following real-time optimization techniques to maximize available WAN bandwidth, extend distances, and improve WAN quality:

  • Latency Mitigation: TCP and other protocol acceleration techniques minimize the effects of latency on application performance and significantly improve application response time across the WAN.
  • Path Conditioning: Adaptive Forward Error Correction (FEC) mitigates packet loss by reducing the need for retransmissions when routers are oversubscribed. Packet Order Correction (POC) is a real-time solution for overcoming out-of-order packet delivery across the WAN.
  • Quality of Service (QoS): Silver Peak appliances employ a variety of QoS and traffic shaping techniques to optimize traffic handling, including advanced queuing, scheduling, and standards based
    packet-marking. VX appliances can honor existing QoS tags or create new policies for granular QoS control.
  • Data Reduction: Each Silver Peak appliance inspects WAN traffic at the byte level and stores copies of content in high-capacity disk drives. Advanced finger-printing techniques recognize repetitive patterns for local delivery. Data Reduction operates at the network layer and supports all IP-based protocols including TCP, UDP and RTP.

metatron Discovery was built as an enterprise big data platform to analyze over 500 TB’s of daily mobile network service data in SK Telecom, South Korea’s No.1 telecommunications provider.

metatron Discovery provides the following unique values :

    Visualize and analyze real big data. The distributed data processing engine of metatron Discovery enables searching, exploration, preparation, visualization and analysis of massive data(over 1 billion records) within a few seconds.
    Easy Self-analytics. With just a few hours of learning, process and analyze your data through metatron Discovery’s intuitive UI and derive valuable insights immediately. Also easily access advanced algorithms created by data scientists through APIs.
    Significantly improve data management capabilities. Through the powerful data lineage management, MDM(master data management) features, IT managers can efficiently manage data resources in the enterprise. Also by monitoring the usage of each table and tracing data flows, you can optimize your big data infrastructure resources.

Fibre Channel SAN appliances offer, including thin provisioning, mirroring and snapshots. StoneFly's snapshot technology is designed to offer quick, efficient point-in-time replicas of SAN volumes for data recovery, testing, business continuity and more. Each delta-based snapshot is a virtual, temporary, and perishable point-in-time image of an active live volume. With small storage requirements and nearly instantaneous creation, snapshots are an integral part of StoneFly's advanced SAN and storage management. Snapshots contain an image of the volume at the exact point-in-time that the snapshot was taken. The snapshot volume appears to any host machine as if it was a regular logical volume and can be mounted as read-only or read-write. Even after changes are made to the original volume, delta-based snapshots preserve a copy exactly as it existed when it was taken. StoneFly remote iSCSI storage hosted in Azure is provisioned exactly like a local drive. Existing Tenable customers can utilize the scanners licensed as part of their Tenable.io or Nessus Manager purchase. Simply create the virtual machine on the Azure Marketplace and then apply Nessus activation license to enable the scanner.

New Tenable customers can purchase Nessus licenses via the Tenable Online Store (www.store.tenable.com) or through an authorized Tenable Reseller (https://www.tenable.com/partners/find-a-reseller).

Teramind UAM: User Activity Monitoring and UEBA (User & Entity Behavior Analytics)

Insider Threat Detection & Prevention

Use Teramind to detect and prevent insider threats from both your employees and third-parties. Automated rules enforce company policy and decrease unproductive behavior. A Test Server

  • TAFPro is the latest method of queuing large numbers of tests in a cloud environment

Data Driven Test Management
  • TAFPro can manage millions of data driven tests

  • No other tool offers out of the box data driven functions for these tools

Subscription - Webserver Auth","description":"

Supported Users

  • Active Directory users
  • Synchronized Azure AD users using Azure Domain Services
  • Local webserver users

Knowledge Security Model

  • KB
  • Library
  • Book

This keep-it-simple version of Theum assumes users have access to all of the documents you place in a book or library or Theum KB. The security properties associated with individual documents is ignored.

Runs with

  • Elasticsearch built-in (free and pre-configured) OR
  • Azure Elastic Cloud Standard (additional cost) OR
  • Self-managed Elastic Kubernetes infrastructure

Notes

  • Knowledge processing services require a minimum of 4 cores and 16 GB RAM
  • May be deployed multiple times for various purposes, for example, one server with at least 4 cores and 16 GB RAM for knowledge processing and one server with 2 cores that serves as a web server for Theum knowledge portals
  • License cannot be used to provide knowledge publishing services for other legal entities.
  • Enterprises with special needs should contact Theum AG directly for special pricing options.

Indicators this version may be right for you...

  • You wish to share knowledge but have no user authentication model or Active Directory
  • You wish to use Active Directory authentication within an established domain or new domain in your IT infrastructure

The cost of running Veeam Cloud Connect for Service Providers to Azure is a combination of the selected software plan charges plus the Azure infrastructure costs for the virtual machines on which you will be running this software. Your Azure infrastructure price might vary if you have enterprise agreements or other discounts.

To ensure our cloud service provider partners are effectively enabled to go to market with us, Veeam offers:

  • Expanded usage rights to license Veeam as a provider to manage and protect third-party data
  • A pay-as-you-grow pricing program that aligns to the recurring revenue model many providers employ to bill their own customers
  • Licenses that unlock data protection and value-added services for any customer, any workload, across any cloud
  • Purpose-built products and partner portals designed to quickly onboard customers, unlock capabilities and make monthly usage reporting painless

For customers, Veeam Cloud Connect components are already included within Veeam Backup & Replication. No additional licensing is required.

To provide Veeam Cloud Connect services, providers must purchase a license key from Veeam Aggregators. Licensing is per virtual machine backed up through Cloud Connect to Azure, per month. If you are not a Veeam Cloud & Service Provider, please visit https://www.veeam.com/service-providers.html to learn more and sign up today.

SlashDB CE is a scalable option suitable for applications large and small.

Start for free on an A0 instance, which is a perfect option for developers and startups to quickly build their minimally viable product (MVP). A0 is not valid for production deployments.

Use a single A-series instance for smaller applications, or launch on larger D-series or G-series instances for upward scalability. Finally, you can deploy multiple instances behind a load balancer for high availability applications on global scale. Contact the vendor if you need help with proper sizing or to request license key more databases/users.

SlashDB offers unmatched shortcut for making data-centric REST APIs. Use it as a backend for web and mobile applications. Use it for modernizing enterprise applications for the cloud too. Leverage it for monetizing data assets too. Whichever the use case, SlashDB CE on Microsoft Azure scales up and out.

Use the "Enterprise" edition if you need customized installation or for multiple databases. Most suitable for larger organizations with heterogeneous database systems and/or looking to migrate legacy client/server three-tier applications to cloud and REST APIs.

Register with the vendor to obtain custom license key at http://www.slashdb.com/request-quote/#unlimited

Connectors can be deployed in several forms. Zscaler distributes a standard virtual machine (VM) image for deployment in enterprise data centers, local “private cloud” environments such as Hyper-V, or “public cloud” environments such as Azure. Additionally, Zscaler provides packages that can be installed on supported Linux distributions. See the list of platforms supported by ZPA.
Connectors may be co-located with your enterprise applications, or they can be deployed in any location that has connectivity to the applications. Typically, they are deployed on network segments that can access secured applications and the ZPA Cloud simultaneously, such as in a DMZ. Note that Connectors only connect outbound; they do not need any inbound “open ports” to operate correctly. Because Connectors are always active, they are also typically deployed in a redundant configuration. However, Connectors never communicate with each other.
